        "s. It argues that just as selection pressure led to animals evolving useful ways of interacting with the natural environment, so also it led to the genetic evolution of advantageous social behavior.     While the term sociobiology originated at least as early as the 1940s, the concept did not gain major recognition until the publication of ": null
