        ". However, there is continued resistance by some researchers over the application of evolutionary models to humans, particularly from within the social sciences, where culture has long been assumed to be the predominant driver of behavior.          Sociobiology is based upon two fundamental premises:   Certain behavioral traits are inherited,   Inherited behavioral traits have been honed by natural selection. Therefore, these traits were probably adaptive in the environment in which the species evolved.     Sociobiology uses ": null
